value.0: Now you will select your proficiencies. All characters are allowed three proficiencies. Some proficiencies are only available to certain class standings.
Select your proficiencies. When you have finished selecting your proficiencies, select "No Options Left."

<StartHighlight>[Wood Gathering]</Start>
Allows you to gather useful wood for the creation of items or placeables.
Requirements: Lower Class Standing.

<StartHighlight>[Tracking]</Start>
Allows you to track creatures.
Requirements: Any Class Standing

<StartHighlight>[Tailoring]</Start>
Allows you to create additional clothing/cloth items.
Requirements: Middle or Lower Class Standing

<StartHighlight>[Fire Building]</Start>
Allows you to build fires that make you warm.
Requirements: Any Class Standing

<StartHighlight>[Smelting]</Start>
This proficiency enables a character to effectively purify metal ores, or combine base metals into refined products such as sophisticated alloys. This proficiency also enables a character to melt down and salvage metals if their crafting roll of 1d20 plus level plus intelligence modifier is successful.
Requirements: None

<StartHighlight>[Siege Engineering]</Start>
Allows you to use siege engines.
Requirements: Any Class Standing

<StartHighlight>[Observation]</Start>
This proficiency enables a character to more effectively determine if someone is disguised. This capability is something of a merit badge among blackcoats and spies for hire.
Requirements: None

<StartHighlight>[Mining]</Start>
Allows you to gather useful ores, metals, and minerals from rock.
Requirements: Lower Class Standing

<StartHighlight>[Masonry]</Start>
Allows you to work stone in order to create placeables or other objects.
Requirements: Middle or Lower Class Standing

<StartHighlight>[Hunting]</Start>
Allows you to hunt animals and gain usable materials from them such as skins.
Requirements: Any Class Standing

<StartHighlight>[History]</Start>
Allows you extra knowledge of history and events both recent and ancient.
Requirements: Upper or Middle Class Standing

<StartHighlight>[Herbalism]</Start>
Allows you to combine and refine natural or unnatural elements into new and exciting combinations.
Requirements: Any Standing

<StartHighlight>[Gunsmithing]</Start>
This proficiency enables a character to make firearms from base crafting materials, as well as make modifications to a firearm without a requiring a crafting roll.
Requirements: None

<StartHighlight>[Deciphering Scripts]</Start>
Allows you to decipher strange scripts in arcane or non-native languages with greater ease.
Requirements: Upper or Middle Class Standing

<StartHighlight>[Disguise]</Start>
This proficiency enables a character to more effectively disguise themselves. This capbility is something of a merit badge among professional killers and spies for hire.
Requirements: None

<StartHighlight>[Carpentry]</Start>
Allows you to perform wood working operations and create placeables or other wood-required items.
Requirements: Middle or Lower Class Standing

<StartHighlight>[Astrology]</Start>
Allows you extra knowledge of the planes and astrological matters.
Requirements: Upper or Middle Class Standing.

<StartHighlight>[Armoring]</Start>
Allows you to craft arms and armor, as well as smelt different kinds of metal.
Requirements: Middle or Lower Class Standing

<StartHighlight>[Anatomy]</Start>
This proficiency represents the study of the anatomy of living things. It enables a character to increase their effective critical hit severity by +2, as well as increase the save DC vs. death for a critical hit effect by +2. Additionally, a character with Anatomy proficiency receives a +2 bonus to heal checks when applying a bandage, and they receive a +2 bonus to hunting checks to recover an organ or other resource.
Requirements: Upper or Middle Class Standing

<StartHighlight>[Alchemy]</Start>
This proficiency enables a character to exploit the hidden properties of alchemical substances. Common uses of alchemical processes include the silvering of a weapon or the refinement of specialized reagents recovered from monsters. An Alchemy check is made by rolling 1d20 plus level plus intelligence modifier.
Requirements: Upper or Middle Class Standing
